OL,3,CGovernment drops Troubles immunity
OL,4,Cappeal
OL,6,FMr Benn said the government would
OL,7,Fcontinue its appeal against the
OL,8,Fjudgment on this specific ground,
OL,9,Fciting the need for clarity in
OL,10,Frelation to how that ruling could
OL,11,Fpotentially affect other government
OL,12,Flegislation in the future.
OL,14,F"Whilst the government is unwavering
OL,15,Fin its commitment to the obligations
OL,16,Funder Article 2(1) of the Windsor
OL,17,FFramework, this judgment has
OL,18,Fpotentially wide-ranging implications
OL,19,Ffor other UK legislation which extends
OL,20,Fto Northern Ireland," he said.
OL,26,@vD@AOU|D@UO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/19
