OL,3,CGovernment drops Troubles immunity
OL,4,Cappeal
OL,6,FThe High Court judgment found that the
OL,7,FICRIR was both independent and capable
OL,8,Fof conducting human rights-compliant
OL,9,Finvestigations. That aspect of the
OL,10,Fjudgment has been appealed by the
OL,11,Fwidow of a Troubles victim.
OL,13,FThe Labour Government has indicated it
OL,14,Fwill not scrap the commission and
OL,15,Finstead work to make changes to its
OL,16,Fstructures.
OL,18,FMr Benn said it would be
OL,19,F"irresponsible" to repeal the entirety
OL,20,Fof the Legacy Act "without anything to
OL,21,Freplace it".
OL,26,@{D@AOU{D@OO]|D@SOU}D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/19
